events.title: Loving the Elderly Life Group Serve Opportunity at Ivy Park
events.description: Looking for a meaningful way for your Life Group to serve together? Ivy Park Assisted Living is welcoming Life Groups to plan their own special event for residents—whether it's an ice cream social, game time, or another fun activity. This is a great opportunity to build relationships, bring joy, and share God's love with the elderly in our community. Gather your group, reach out to Ivy Park directly, and create a memorable experience for the residents! Sign up on our interest list to receive Ivy Park's contact information. Thank you for serving with your Life Group!

events.title: Marine Ministry Sunday Shuttle Service Interest
events.description: Our church loves to serve our local Marines. One day a week, these men and women get to come and be a part of a community that loves and supports them. Using the Outreach vehicles, we have the opportunity to provide transportation from Camp Pendleton to church every Sunday and back to base. Please register to let us know if you would be interested in serving our Marines in this way.

events.title: Strong Families/Short Term Host Family Interest List
events.description: This is an interest list for people interested in becoming Short Term Host Families for the Strong Families Program through Olivecrest. Olivecrest is a non-profit organization dedicated to preventing child abuse by strengthening, equipping, and restoring children and families in crisis, one life at a time. Host families would help parents in crisis by watching their children for a short period of time (days or weeks) in the host's home. Support and online training through Olivecrest will be provided to host families.
